{
  "texts": [
    "Their classification accuracy of 88.9% achieved an area under the ROC curve of 0.973.",
    "41 tackled the issue of the absence of specialized COVID-19 chest X-ray images by developing a patch-based CNN approach for coronavirus assessment with a manageable number of trainable parameters.",
    "Their suggested model included a pre-processing step to normalize data heterogeneities and bias, a segmentation network to extract the lung region, and a classification network for patch-by-patch training and inference.",
    "The model achieved sensitivities of 90%, 93%, and 100% for normal, pneumonia, and COVID-19 images, respectively, with corresponding precision values of 95.7%, 90.3%, and 76.9%.",
    "Nigam et al."
  ]
}